<p>El Paso residents have access to several valuable solar incentives that significantly reduce the cost of installation. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost, including equipment and installation, through 2032. This credit steps down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034 before expiring for residential installations. Texas does not impose state income tax, so residents cannot benefit from additional state tax credits, but the state does offer property tax exemptions for solar installations, meaning the added home value from solar panels won't increase property tax assessments. El Paso Electric occasionally offers rebate programs for solar customers, though these vary by year and are typically first-come, first-served. Additionally, Texas has strong net metering policies that allow solar customers to receive full retail credit for excess energy sent back to the grid.</p>

